# API Spring Rules

Package root: `com.highsteak.api`.

## Layering

```
controller → service → repository → domain
dto/         (records for HTTP I/O, separate from entities)
```

- Controllers: mapping, `@Valid`, `@PreAuthorize`, delegate to services
- Services: business logic, `@Transactional` where needed
- Repositories: Spring Data interfaces only
- Domain: JPA entities in `domain/`
- DTOs: Java records in `dto/` (e.g. `AuthDtos`, `PostDtos`)

## Conventions

- Use Lombok `@RequiredArgsConstructor` for constructor injection
- Global errors: `GlobalExceptionHandler` → `ApiError` record
- File uploads: multipart in controller, storage in service, URLs as `/uploads/...`
- User IDs are `UUID`; post and comment IDs are `UUID` (see `api-ids.mdc`)

## Context path

`server.servlet.context-path=/api`. Controller mappings:

```java
@RequestMapping("/auth")   // → http://host:8080/api/auth
```

## Examples

```java
// BAD — entity returned directly from controller
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public User getUser(@PathVariable UUID id) {
    return userRepository.findById(id).orElseThrow();
}

// GOOD — DTO from service
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public AuthDtos.UserSummary getUser(@PathVariable UUID id) {
    return userAdminService.getUser(id);
}
```

```java
// BAD — duplicate validation in service and DTO
public void create(String title) {
    if (title == null || title.isBlank()) throw ...
}

// GOOD — @NotBlank on DTO record, @Valid on controller param
public record CreateRequest(@NotBlank String title) {}
```

